  "decision": {
    "robust_read": "MindSpeed-style hot-helper is reproduced as a real 20-step advantage. At MBS4 it gives +29.5% late-step tok/GPU/s and saves 48.87 GiB peak memory versus no helper. More importantly, it moves the usable fit boundary from no-helper MBS4 to hot-helper MBS8.",
    "current_best_row": "MBS8 hot-helper top-8 with attention-only AC and checkpoint_enable=false: steps 13-20 average 8632.78 tok/GPU/s, 69062.25 node tok/s, 395.37 TFLOPs/GPU, peak 256.19 GiB.",
    "not_promoted_rows": [
      "MBS4 no-helper is stable but much slower and higher-memory than MBS4 hot-helper.",
      "MBS4 hot-helper is stable and useful as an A/B control, but MBS8 hot-helper is the throughput row.",
      "MBS8 no-helper fails before first metric with integrated memory faults.",
      "MBS16 hot-helper fails before first metric in sparse-MLA/indexer forward on an 8 GiB allocation."
    ],
    "next_mori_native_target": "Preserve the standard-EP hot/cold/helper owner-compact layout, then make the compact helper/normal dispatch-combine ABI native in MORI without dense selected-order hot-weight adapters or extra post-plan materialization."
